<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204898">Ayiar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uarleanna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arleanna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WERE YOU NOT<br>ENTERTAINED?!</span><br>  Posts: 536<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 12:52:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~jakecj7/EQ/Sphynx4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In deference to the wheelchair bandit</span><hr size=1> That entire saga is pretty funny, but encouraging posting real life info is sad. You state in the title you are showing respect to our server's computer stolen thread but in that entire episode, which involved real life items by the way, Bowynn never endorsed the posting of real life info so a bunch of retarded messageboard geeks could get thier jollies crank calling her or her employers. That fact that your server does is the strongest evidence yet that EQ is in serious need of a moron enema.<br>
