<br>
Sargy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ucroneustitanis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Croneus Titanis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 610<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 2:36:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.animatedgif.net/cartoons/flhumpy_e0.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In deference to the wheelchair bandit</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Arleanna on this case. I'm not sure if you read through the entire post, but this guy is no joke. Normally I'd agree that the annoymity of EQ permits people to act in a way they might not ordinarily act in RL when faced with a similar incident. <br>
<br>
But this guy is not only malicious, and vindictive in the game, but equally as disturbed in RL. I mean he not only robbed his guild of their entire funds, causing a lot of anger and fury with the members of that community, but he also was involved with a RL computer scam 10 years ago when he was a high school student, that ripped off nearly 36 thousand dollars. He wasn't found guilty of the charges, but his name was still publically announced as one of the suspects. And all this information was posted on those messageboards, along with his address, phone number, employer, even his picture. <br>
<br>
And this guy was not to be taken lightly. He was dead serious not only in his threats to his online ex-guildmates about what he'd do to their stuff if they kept pushing him, but he swore &quot;with every fiber in my body&quot; that he would defend himself if anyone tried to track him down. He said he would be &quot;amazed and dissapointed&quot; at the same time if someone came to his apartment complex (which they also posted the info for) and tried to mess with him. He warned that he was armed and swore that someone would die if he was attacked. I mean the people on that board took things way to far. <br>
<br>
This guy is uncaring, unfeeling, malicious, and mentally unstable. And the people wanted blood. He doesn't need stalkers and enemies, he needs therapy. We always talk about two wrongs not making a right and this was a clear case of that. And I agree that you deal with issues in the realm where they originated from. I mean this guy might easily have been a convicted felon, but in the realm of EQ, he's just an un-sportsman. It's important to make that distinction. <br>
<br>
None of his other shady history would ever have been brought into play if everyone (including those people who weren't even involved) treated EQ for what it is; a game. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162713" target="_blank"><b>Croneus Titanis</b></a><Br>
<b>60th Warlock</b><Br> <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg" target="_blank"><b>The Tribunal</b></a><center><img src="http://croneus.freeservers.com/images/cat.jpg" border="0"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/urynnia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rynnia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 753<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 4:03:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In deference to the wheelchair bandit</span><hr size=1> I've not even clicked the link.<br>
<br>
As far as the analogies they are off base and irrelevant.   Someone stealing a football has nothing to do with online activity.  I would fully understand if a person who acted in the fashion which you illustrate was deemed &quot;unstable.&quot;<br>
<br>
Online staying online and RL staying RL is a noble concept, but as realistic as expecting people to play by the rules set forth in a consequenceless society.  Sure there's a line between the two, to some extent, but it's dotted and far from solid.  Slandering someone online should have the same consequences as slandering someone in real life.  Stealing from an individual or group online should have the same consequences as stealing from a group or individual in real life.   All that separates on online community (and I use the term loosely) from a real life community is that little wire.<br>
<br>
Have I looked up people's RL info?  Yeah.  How long does it take?  5 minutes.   Have I posted RL info?  Yep.  Why?  One was a liar to the point it was getting obnoxious, and they had given me enough grief in the past, accusing me of doing what they were doing themselves.   One was a con artist, ripping people off for large amounts of money.  The posting of their RL info was limited to a messageboard devoted to tracking down this individual, so that people could pursue the person to get their money back.<br>
<br>
Sick?  Obsessive?  I'd agree with ya were I posting RL info left and right, or if anyone who wronged me online I  instantly ran off to pull up their precious secret information.  I don't  : )  My personal feelings on the matter is that it is a sick mentality wanting and or needing that line to be there.  Wanting or needing for an escape.  Wanting or needing an alternate reality which does not blend with real life.  Sure, EQ is a game.  A game which people play in their spare time in real life.   Sure, the internet is a tool.  A tool which people use in real life.  This isn't Mr. Roger's Neigborhood land of make believe here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/urynnia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rynnia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 754<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 4:16:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In deference to the wheelchair bandit</span><hr size=1> &quot;If some person from AT&amp;T calls you every night getting you to switch to AT&amp;T long distance do you finally go bezerk, find her name and address and post them to<br>
                                           every messageboard you can find? &quot;Hey everyone! This bitch is bothering me at home, let's all call her!&quot; As funny as that sounds I hope you can see that it is<br>
                                           crossing the line.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yeah that'd be a great solution.  It's not crossing the line, assuming you asked for her to stop and she did not.  Why, if I was the one being called in this situation, should I have to be the one to be inconvenienced in this matter? Alot easier to toss it right back at her, rather than endure continuing unwelcome phone calls.  Do you realize how difficult it is to get this kind of shit to stop if it is happening?   You can change your phone number, which is a MAJOR inconvenience and costs money.  You can get the police involved, and they certainly have better things to do with their time.  Going this route will take you damn near forever as well.<br>
<br>
Making a quick post takes all of a minute, and problem solved.<br>
<br>
Or you can just deal with the phone calls for as long as she wishes to keep calling you, wasting your time.  People are too soft. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udeeho81.showPublicProfile?language=EN>deeho81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/02 4:52:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: In deference to the wheelchair bandit</span><hr size=1> you're fucking dense, Rynnia.  wow.<br>
<br>
