<br>
Found his info, called his house, got his &quot;mom&quot; on the phone.  She freaked out, put me on phone with &quot;dad&quot; who was wondering where his son had been getting &quot;all this money.&quot;  Walked &quot;dad&quot; through his son's files on his computer, confirmed what he was doing, &quot;dad&quot; flips, much smashing is heard on the other end of the phone, &quot;dad&quot; apologizes and says he'll have his son call me.  Kid calls me about 30 minutes later.  I informed him of what was going on, he acknowledged it, I also informed him that I would be providing those he defrauded with the means to contact him, he did not object.<br>
<br>
Turned the rest of the info I had over to the proper authorities, who contacted me later to ask questions.  Helped as many people as I could get their money back, and that was the end of that.<br>
<br>
Pretty fucked up of me.... what the fuck was I thinking?<br>
<br>
&quot; How would you feel if you posted some information that got some injured or killed?&quot;<br>
<br>
Posting information does not get anyone injured or killed.  Kinda like blaming a brewery for causing a drunk driving accident.  It's the individual's poor judgment that creates the action, not the provision of the tool.<br>
<br>
&quot; Its okay though right, because &quot;Anyone&quot; can find it, but the rub is not &quot;Anyone&quot; is posting it, you are, so you are responsible for any reprecussations taken from your irresponsible act.&quot;<br>
<br>
